“You’re not that Busy Babe 🤦🏽‍♀️” was the title of my event I curated in partnership with @jumpman23 for #womenshistorymonth I know too many women who are in need of self-love but often prioritize themselves last, why?

I like to curate my events by connecting people who 

1. May not know each other but I feel would make good friends
2. Who need a lil TLC and community 

In true Elyse fashion we talked through our ~feelings~ with an activity that asked “What 3 things you could use more of in life and how will that affect you positively?” I got this question from @cheynotshy and it’s helped me shift vanity needs vs ACTUAL needs

We enjoyed cupcakes by @eatgoodnyc that rep’d the 1st 2 women to create their own Jordan @vashtie @alealimay & everyone received a Jordan basketball trophy and tagged what their greatest skills are 🏀 

I think I should make “You’re not that Busy Babe” a series, 🤔 what do you think?

Thank you to @foreverytable for catering the event 🥗 & @sipmichaellavelle for giving us something to sip 🍷

@sadgirlsclub is currently raising funds for our 1:1 therapy scholarship program Remedy 2.0

*Our goal is to provide 1000 hours of free therapy
*To ensure Remedy is sustainable and to honor an exchange of wellness services, our therapists are paid a competitive rate for every session
*Grantees are selected on a quarterly basis
*Grantees receive 2 sessions of therapy month for a full year with an opportunity to renew

Africa has been on my bucket list for years but with motherhood & running @sadgirlsclub it’s been hard to find time to prioritize it. I slowed down with content creation mid 2023 to focus on what’s next for myself, family & the industry of wellness, I never wanted to be a slave to the algorithm and thought opportunities and trip offerings would slow down while I recharged my mind 🧠 

Forever grateful for this experience with the most inspiring group of creatives. I’ve never cried at the end of a brand trip😭 what @olamideaolowe has created is bigger than us. In January 2020 @olamideaolowe and I had a call. Before a single product was sold, @topicals committed an incredible donation to @sadgirlsclub and has been rockin with us ever since

Little did she know I was struggling with postpartum depression, and unknowingly—a pandemic was creeping up in the coming months. As a fellow CEO I have so much admiration and love for O’s work. There have been plenty of moments in my career of false support to leverage others agendas. To think that she’s always showed up to support when billionaires pretended to care and fell through *cough cough*
